&lt;p>The Institute?s strategy has two strands. First, to organise a series of lectures on public economics aimed at sixth formers and undergraduates, drawing on their expertise in areas such as policy evaluation, labour supply, pensions and saving, inequality, public spending and productivity, as well as introducing and exploring economic theory. These will build on the annual IFS&amp;nbsp;(Institute for Fiscal Studies)&amp;nbsp;series of Oxford and Cambridge public economics lectures, but broaden the potential audience by holding a one-day event in a large London venue, providing funding to subsidise travel for students coming from further afield.&lt;/p> 
&lt;p>IFS will also expand the current section of its website known as Fiscal Facts. They will improve the coverage of the tax tables and add to the briefing notes on the tax and benefit systems to include a survey of local government finance.&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2007-04-30</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2006-04-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>26138</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs><gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:description>The public finance</gtr:description><gtr:form>A talk or presentation</gtr:form><gtr:geographicReach>National</gtr:geographicReach><gtr:id>61274DA7-934A-4028-BA1D-D86830AD416A</gtr:id><gtr:impact>This presentation gives an overview of public finances, discussing the framework within which public finance decisions are made in the UK.</gtr:impact><gtr:partOfOfficialScheme>false</gtr:partOfOfficialScheme><gtr:primaryAudience>Other academic audiences (collaborators, peers etc.)</gtr:primaryAudience><gtr:url>http://www.ifs.org.uk/conferences/pubfin_frayne.ppt</gtr:url><gtr:year>2008</gtr:year></gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:description>Geeks bearing graphs? : economists and economics at IFS</gtr:description><gtr:form>A talk or presentation</gtr:form><gtr:geographicReach>Regional</gtr:geographicReach><gtr:id>1337A2BD-0AF5-46C3-95F7-38B18010B6A6</gtr:id><gtr:impact>This presentation was given at the IFS Public Economics Lectures on 19th March 2007. The aim of these lectures was to illustrate to students of economics how economics is applied to policy.</gtr:impact><gtr:partOfOfficialScheme>false</gtr:partOfOfficialScheme><gtr:primaryAudience>Public/other audiences</gtr:primaryAudience><gtr:url>http://www.ifs.